00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:01.570
Having finished the report,
the lights were turned off

00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:03.790
and everyone left the office.

00:18:04.355 --> 00:18:05.045
Options.

00:18:05.435 --> 00:18:08.225
A, the lights were turned off by him.

00:18:08.645 --> 00:18:10.955
B, he turned off the lights.

00:18:11.225 --> 00:18:13.325
C turning off the lights.

00:18:13.565 --> 00:18:16.295
D, the office lights were turned off.

00:18:16.985 --> 00:18:20.015
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:18:21.090 --> 00:18:21.900
Solution.

00:18:22.530 --> 00:18:24.390
Let's tackle this one, my friends.

00:18:24.780 --> 00:18:28.260
Step one, identify the dangling modifier.

00:18:28.710 --> 00:18:30.540
See that introductory phrase?

00:18:30.810 --> 00:18:35.340
Having finished the report, it
implies that someone finished the

00:18:35.340 --> 00:18:40.050
report, but then the subject of
the main clause is the lights.

00:18:40.470 --> 00:18:42.150
Can lights finish a report?

00:18:42.510 --> 00:18:43.110
No.

00:18:43.290 --> 00:18:45.180
Unless it's a sci-fi movie.

00:18:45.510 --> 00:18:49.350
This my friends, is a classic
case of a dangling modifier.

00:18:49.970 --> 00:18:53.300
Step two, determine the implied subject.

00:18:53.780 --> 00:18:57.320
The phrase clearly implies a
person finished the report.

00:18:57.650 --> 00:18:59.600
That's our implied subject.

00:19:00.230 --> 00:19:06.770
Step three, evaluate the options option
A. The lights were turned off by him.

00:19:07.010 --> 00:19:10.610
Still has the lights as the
subject of the main clause.

00:19:11.030 --> 00:19:15.140
The hymn comes later, making
it still a bit awkward and not

00:19:15.140 --> 00:19:16.760
fully resolving that dangle.

00:19:17.544 --> 00:19:21.085
Option B, he turned off
the lights is perfect.

00:19:21.445 --> 00:19:26.754
It correctly identifies he the person
who finished the report as the subject

00:19:26.754 --> 00:19:31.495
of the main clause, making the sentence
grammatically correct and clear.

00:19:31.825 --> 00:19:32.725
No more dangling here.

00:19:33.865 --> 00:19:38.665
And option C. Turning off the lights
is just another participant phrase.

00:19:38.995 --> 00:19:43.795
It doesn't give us a clear subject for
the action of finishing the report, so

00:19:43.945 --> 00:19:49.375
not much help and Option D, the office
lights were turned off, is pretty

00:19:49.375 --> 00:19:53.815
similar to option A, and doesn't fix
our dangling modifier issue at all.

00:19:54.570 --> 00:19:58.320
Step four, conclude the
best option, my friends.

00:19:58.500 --> 00:20:03.689
Option B provides a clear and logical
subject for both the introductory

00:20:03.689 --> 00:20:05.459
phrase and the main clause.

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:09.360
It's concise, correct and
clears up all confusion.

00:20:09.780 --> 00:20:13.949
Correct answer is option B, example three.

