00:20:46.365 --> 00:20:47.235
Solution.

00:20:47.745 --> 00:20:49.125
Last one, my friends.

00:20:49.275 --> 00:20:50.475
Let's nail it.

00:20:51.045 --> 00:20:54.735
Step one, identify the parallel structure.

00:20:55.185 --> 00:20:58.995
We have a classic pair of core
relative conjunctions here.

00:20:59.295 --> 00:21:03.555
Not only, but also these
guys are like twins.

00:21:03.765 --> 00:21:05.775
They demand parallel structure.

00:21:06.225 --> 00:21:11.505
This means whatever grammatical
form follows, not only must match

00:21:11.505 --> 00:21:16.845
the form following, but also
step two, analyze the original

00:21:16.845 --> 00:21:19.635
sentence in our original sentence.

00:21:19.815 --> 00:21:25.395
Not only is followed by talented in
music, which is an adjective phrase, but

00:21:25.755 --> 00:21:32.445
but also is followed by in painting a
prepositional phrase, see the mismatch?

00:21:32.670 --> 00:21:34.200
They are not parallel.

00:21:34.740 --> 00:21:42.000
Step three, evaluate the options option
A, but also talented in painting makes

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:43.980
the structure perfectly parallel.

00:21:44.340 --> 00:21:50.820
Now we have talented in music and talented
in painting both adjective phrases.

00:21:51.180 --> 00:21:57.905
This is what we call perfect harmony,
option B. But also paints well, changes

00:21:57.905 --> 00:22:02.645
the structure to a verb phrase, which
just doesn't match talented in music.

00:22:02.795 --> 00:22:09.755
So no go option C, but also in
painting as well is redundant because

00:22:09.755 --> 00:22:14.525
as well adds nothing new and it
still doesn't achieve that beautiful

00:22:14.525 --> 00:22:17.195
parallelism with the adjective phrase.

00:22:17.610 --> 00:22:22.260
Option D, but also good at
painting is an adjective phrase.

00:22:22.320 --> 00:22:27.930
Yes, but talented in music and good
at painting aren't as precisely

00:22:27.930 --> 00:22:30.900
parallel or as elegant as option A.

00:22:31.170 --> 00:22:33.180
We are looking for the best option.

00:22:33.180 --> 00:22:33.810
Remember?

00:22:34.350 --> 00:22:37.080
Step four, conclude the best option.

00:22:37.260 --> 00:22:40.800
So my friends option A
is the clear winner here.

00:22:41.189 --> 00:22:45.570
It provides the most grammatically
correct and perfectly parallel

00:22:45.570 --> 00:22:50.489
structure, making the sentence
clear, balanced, and a joy to read.

00:22:50.939 --> 00:22:54.389
Correct answer is option A. Thank you.

